1
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:06,400
Ruining your audition doesn't mean you've ruined your life. Why didn't you answer the phone all day?

2
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:09,890
I thought you were mentally out, or hiding yourself.

3
00:00:09,890 --> 00:00:14,550
What do you mean hiding? I've been stuck in the practice room since this morning.

4
00:00:14,550 --> 00:00:19,070
Why did you go to the practice room? It's better to get some rest when you're mentally out.

5
00:00:19,070 --> 00:00:23,170
Come here after you finish your driving job. If you don't attend the club meeting, you have to pay double dues.

6
00:00:23,170 --> 00:00:28,120
- What? No way. Since when?
- Since today.

7
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:33,340
Ah, these guys are really... Hey, wait right there.

8
00:00:42,050 --> 00:00:46,270
Customer, are you hot? Should I open the window?

9
00:00:46,270 --> 00:00:52,430
Sorry, Boss. It was hard for me to live. It's...

10
00:00:52,430 --> 00:00:58,620
- all my fault. I have three children.
- Customer?

11
00:00:58,620 --> 00:01:02,870
Boss, please forgive me just this once.

12
00:01:02,870 --> 00:01:05,810
Ah, what are you doing?

13
00:01:06,610 --> 00:01:08,270
Round about midnight

14
00:01:08,270 --> 00:01:11,020
Hungarian Dance

15
00:01:58,050 --> 00:02:01,200
One 500 ml glass of beer, please.

16
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:09,040
The meeting of the Sinyeong Orchestra Club is here...

17
00:02:09,040 --> 00:02:13,350
Yi Yeong, here, here.

18
00:02:13,350 --> 00:02:18,660
Everyone, let's welcome the 23rd General Manager of our Sinyeong Orchestra Club.

19
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:24,780
Long time no see!

20
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:27,080
- Why are you so late?
- Right!

21
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:30,970
Drink it. Drink it. Drink it. Drink it.

22
00:02:30,970 --> 00:02:35,580
Until you make me dance. Look at my shoulders. They are dislocated.

23
00:02:35,580 --> 00:02:38,500
Whoever loses must drink it up.

24
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:40,100
- Do you want it?
- We want it!

25
00:02:40,100 --> 00:02:42,420
- Do you want it?
- We want it!

26
00:02:42,420 --> 00:02:45,360
Okay, let's do it!

27
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:51,570
Kiss, kiss, kiss. Thank you.

28
00:02:51,570 --> 00:02:52,820
Let’s do this.

29
00:02:52,820 --> 00:02:55,560
It's nothing to be on the top.

30
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:59,240
The Symphony orchestra I work at runs only on local grants.

31
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:02,430
The salary is just over the minimum wage

32
00:03:02,430 --> 00:03:06,310
and I have to compete with my juniors. It's very hard for me.

33
00:03:06,310 --> 00:03:09,150
Hey, still you get to perform.

34
00:03:09,150 --> 00:03:15,050
It's been three years since I was fired from the orchestra and became a coach preparing students for the entrance exam.

35
00:03:15,050 --> 00:03:18,850
Living this life... it's really hell.

36
00:03:18,850 --> 00:03:20,750
Hell!

37
00:03:20,750 --> 00:03:24,720
What's with all of you today? At least you guys have a job related to your major.

38
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:29,700
I've been playing cello for 20 years and I still sell shoes online.

39
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:35,290
- Hey, let's drink!
- Let's drink!

40
00:03:35,990 --> 00:03:39,060
Hey, you!

41
00:03:39,060 --> 00:03:44,810
I'm so envious of you, you and you too.

42
00:03:44,810 --> 00:03:48,030
I'm envious of all of you.

43
00:03:48,030 --> 00:03:53,190
Why are you—  Hey, are you drunk?

44
00:03:53,190 --> 00:03:56,700
I'm going to talk about myself.

45
00:03:56,700 --> 00:04:02,110
I've done seventeen auditions and failed every single time. I've never studied abroad and my qualifications are lacking.

46
00:04:02,110 --> 00:04:04,570
I can't even dream of coaching students for the college entrance exam.

47
00:04:04,570 --> 00:04:08,910
I've been a substitute driver for so long.

48
00:04:11,090 --> 00:04:16,010
Yesterday, I went to an audition, I dropped my mallet and I fell down, too.

49
00:04:16,010 --> 00:04:21,320
And, you know what? Blood started pouring down from my nose.

50
00:04:24,380 --> 00:04:27,530
But  for me, it's okay.

51
00:04:27,530 --> 00:04:30,800
I still have a dream

52
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:35,500
and a cute boyfriend who loves me.

53
00:04:35,590 --> 00:04:39,800
Yes, Hong Yi Yeong is the winner. You are awesome. Everyone applaud!

54
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:43,270
- Right!
- You are awesome!

55
00:04:43,270 --> 00:04:47,040
Kids, what is life?  Eat and die!

56
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:50,040
- All right.
- Let's drink.

57
00:04:52,230 --> 00:04:56,800
- So cool.
- Thank you.

58
00:05:03,590 --> 00:05:06,360
Choi Seo Ju?

59
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:12,290
I also received a message from Choi Seo Ju. What is it? You too?

60
00:05:12,290 --> 00:05:15,050
"Caught having an affair."

61
00:05:16,890 --> 00:05:19,920
- "Yi Yeong's boyfriend"?
- Incredible!

62
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:22,490
Oh, this too, seriously!

63
00:05:22,490 --> 00:05:25,450
Hong Yi Yeong?

64
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:28,490
She is coming!

65
00:05:31,470 --> 00:05:33,820
Aigoo.

66
00:05:36,260 --> 00:05:41,780
I stepped out for a second, and what happened to the mood?

67
00:05:41,780 --> 00:05:44,660
We need to drink!

68
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:55,770
Guys, I'm fine. I'm happy.

69
00:05:55,770 --> 00:06:01,700
I still have my dream and the love of my life.

70
00:06:05,310 --> 00:06:09,500
- Hey, hey!
- No, no!

71
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:12,300
Not true, you know that Seo Ju is a liar!

72
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:14,890
- Right!
- Right, she lies all the time.

73
00:06:14,890 --> 00:06:17,580
- She is strange.
- She is lying.

74
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:21,330
What is this? What's wrong?

75
00:06:23,230 --> 00:06:25,360
"It's really daebak!

76
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:29,800
I discovered violinist Ha Eun Ju is having an affair.

77
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:35,340
They took the elevator at Myeongsin Hotel. The man is...

78
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:43,940
Hong Yi Yeong's boyfriend, Mun Jae Hyeong!

79
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:50,170
Yi Yeong, Yi Yeong, stand up!

80
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:55,900
Damn, I'm going to kill them! Hey, Yi Yeong, are you alright?

81
00:07:08,130 --> 00:07:11,100
I can't believe it.

82
00:07:14,460 --> 00:07:18,970
Rock-a-bye baby, go to sleep.

83
00:07:19,780 --> 00:07:23,720
You are sleeping so well.

84
00:07:48,430 --> 00:07:50,560
Is it good?

85
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:53,010
Yes, it's even better because my noona bought it.

86
00:07:53,010 --> 00:07:57,630
But you are sure you don't want to eat? Should we order one more serving?

87
00:07:57,630 --> 00:08:01,860
Hm, no, no. I'm on diet, I told you.

88
00:08:01,860 --> 00:08:04,930
You don't need to diet.

89
00:08:04,930 --> 00:08:12,230
No, I don't want to get fat. Eat up, eat up everything.

90
00:08:13,730 --> 00:08:15,810
It's delicious.

91
00:08:18,410 --> 00:08:22,450
That looks so good! Meat!

92
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:30,230
That looks really delicious!

93
00:08:32,040 --> 00:08:35,940
You bastard!

94
00:08:39,650 --> 00:08:43,830
I know that I told you to eat everything...

95
00:08:45,010 --> 00:08:48,520
But did you have to actually eat everything?

96
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:56,330
Are you the only one with a mouth? I also have a mouth!

97
00:08:57,690 --> 00:09:03,080
♫ I can't have meat, I can't get married. ♫

98
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:07,480
♫ What a spiteful person. ♫

99
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:09,520
♫ What a spiteful person. ♫

100
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:13,000
- Let's go home, there is meat.
- Who are you?

101
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:17,410
Hey. Hey, you!

102
00:09:17,410 --> 00:09:20,280
Why is a stranger...

103
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:22,520
bothering me?

104
00:09:28,630 --> 00:09:32,280
Ugh. You again?

105
00:09:35,590 --> 00:09:40,360
Why are you so loud when you're drunk? You'll wake up the whole neighborhood.

106
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:43,020
Go home already.

107
00:09:43,020 --> 00:09:45,300
Hey. Hey, you!

108
00:09:45,300 --> 00:09:47,820
Look here!

109
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:51,330
I said, look here!

110
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:56,530
Why do you care about what I do, huh?

111
00:09:56,530 --> 00:10:00,160
Whether I cry or not, whether I act rashly or

112
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:03,250
at what time I add egg to my ramen...

113
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:08,610
You have to add the egg when the ramen
is almost done for it to taste good.

114
00:10:08,610 --> 00:10:09,520
What is this?

115
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:10,790
My phone number.

116
00:10:10,790 --> 00:10:12,110
I'm looking for a part-time job.

117
00:10:12,110 --> 00:10:16,090
I can do errands.

118
00:10:16,090 --> 00:10:19,670
That’s right.

119
00:10:19,670 --> 00:10:23,860
Where are you going, you conman who scams people with a thousand won?

120
00:10:23,860 --> 00:10:25,430
I'm going home, so what?

121
00:10:25,430 --> 00:10:29,510
Home? Where do you live to be walking this way?

122
00:10:29,510 --> 00:10:31,180
This is the way to my house.

123
00:10:31,180 --> 00:10:36,130
Go easy on the alcohol next time. Are you the only one allowed to live here?

124
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:40,600
Where do you think you're going?

125
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:44,890
Don't go!

126
00:10:44,890 --> 00:10:47,660
This is the way to my house, don't go!

127
00:10:51,410 --> 00:10:54,460
Did you scoff at me?

128
00:10:57,500 --> 00:11:00,050
Fine. Scoff.

129
00:11:00,050 --> 00:11:03,640
Scoff! Scoff at me!

130
00:11:04,710 --> 00:11:09,980
I deserve to be scoffed at.

131
00:11:09,980 --> 00:11:13,280
I totally deserve it.

132
00:11:16,260 --> 00:11:20,630
A really cheap life.

133
00:11:33,130 --> 00:11:38,650
No one deserves to be scoffed at.

134
00:11:49,490 --> 00:11:52,090
Woah, what the—

135
00:11:52,090 --> 00:11:53,280
What are you doing?

136
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:56,240
Do you... with me?

137
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:59,780
What? I can't hear you.

138
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:04,000
Do you want to sleep with me?

139
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:06,740
Sleep with me.

140
00:12:06,740 --> 00:12:08,620
Sleep with me, okay?

141
00:12:08,620 --> 00:12:12,200
Let's sleep together, already!

142
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:15,210
Let's sleep together!

143
00:12:16,140 --> 00:12:19,200
Please sleep with me.

144
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:21,760
Sleep with me!

145
00:12:49,760 --> 00:12:51,330
Hello?

146
00:12:51,330 --> 00:12:54,250
It's me, Eun Ju. Come out for a second.

147
00:12:54,250 --> 00:12:57,360
Should I come there, or do you want to come to me?

148
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:00,930
Ha Eun Ju

149
00:13:18,190 --> 00:13:22,010
Don't be afraid, Hong Yi Yeong. You can yell as much as you want.

150
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:53,460
It's for you. It's apparently your favorite.

151
00:13:53,460 --> 00:13:55,250
According to Jae Hyeong.

152
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:59,370
I heard Choi Seo Ju exposed everything yesterday.

153
00:13:59,370 --> 00:14:01,190
They must have badmouthed me a lot.

154
00:14:01,190 --> 00:14:03,430
Is that what you're worried about?

155
00:14:03,430 --> 00:14:05,900
That you will be gossiped about?

156
00:14:07,460 --> 00:14:11,660
Of course not. I’m used to people saying bad things behind my back.

157
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:14,920
I talked to Jae Hyeong, but he apparently has no plans of breaking up with you.

158
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,590
What about you?

159
00:14:17,630 --> 00:14:21,480
I don't plan on meeting him anymore either.

160
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:27,640
So let’s just forget about everything that happened yesterday. Of course, it would've been better if you'd never come to know it.

161
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:30,130
Are you kidding me right now?

162
00:14:30,130 --> 00:14:34,010
He must’ve been a one-night stand to you, but to me...

163
00:14:34,750 --> 00:14:37,550
To me, he’s one of the few precious people—

164
00:14:37,550 --> 00:14:42,630
If he was that precious to you, you should’ve made sure he didn’t cheat.

165
00:14:42,630 --> 00:14:44,510
Don’t you agree?

166
00:14:44,510 --> 00:14:46,700
I called you out to help you two reconcile.

167
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:50,690
I set this up for you two, so the rest is up to you.

168
00:14:53,180 --> 00:14:55,290
I’ll pay for my drink.

169
00:14:56,110 --> 00:14:58,030
Do as you please.

170
00:15:11,580 --> 00:15:12,710
Noona...

171
00:15:12,710 --> 00:15:15,040
Don’t call me that.

172
00:15:16,190 --> 00:15:17,720
I don’t want to hear it.

173
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:19,960
Noona!

174
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:22,870
I told you not to call me that.

175
00:15:25,380 --> 00:15:28,070
That jacket you’re wearing...

176
00:15:28,070 --> 00:15:34,410
cost 800,000 won (about $650). It’s 800,000, you jerk.

177
00:15:36,770 --> 00:15:39,980
I bought it on a 10-month installment plan.
Do you know that?

178
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:44,950
You already know how hard I work to make ends meet.

179
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:49,960
But you've never even contacted me.

180
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:53,030
We’re you out of reach because you were busy cheating?

181
00:15:54,490 --> 00:15:57,270
How could you wear what I bought you and sleep with my friend?

182
00:15:57,270 --> 00:16:00,100
How? How could you do that to me?

183
00:16:00,100 --> 00:16:04,140
I... I also did my part.

184
00:16:05,350 --> 00:16:09,280
- What?
- Even though I’m exhausted, you wake me up in the middle of the night saying you can’t sleep.

185
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:13,280
And this jacket, you’re the one who bought it for me.

186
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:15,830
You apologized and told me it’s for waking me up every night.

187
00:16:15,830 --> 00:16:21,170
Did you really even like me? Didn’t you just need someone to help you fall asleep?

188
00:16:25,490 --> 00:16:27,940
Take it off. I said take it off.

189
00:16:27,940 --> 00:16:29,790
Take it off.

190
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:32,790
Take it off!

191
00:16:33,530 --> 00:16:36,250
I can’t believe you just said that!

192
00:16:36,250 --> 00:16:39,870
Who the hell do you think you are? Who the hell do you think you are!

193
00:16:39,870 --> 00:16:43,910
You made me spend all the money I earned and you slept with my friend.

194
00:16:43,910 --> 00:16:48,770
And what? You’re asking me if I really liked you?

195
00:16:48,770 --> 00:16:50,690
Noona, I’m sorry. I’m really sorry.

196
00:16:50,690 --> 00:16:52,790
Don’t come near me!

197
00:16:57,910 --> 00:17:00,350
Just pay for my drink.

198
00:17:02,390 --> 00:17:04,410
Noona!

199
00:17:08,070 --> 00:17:09,930
Noona! I was wrong!

200
00:17:09,930 --> 00:17:12,390
Can we please talk, Noona?

201
00:17:12,390 --> 00:17:14,270
Noona!

202
00:17:27,550 --> 00:17:33,920
A genius once said... “love is a waste of time”.

203
00:17:35,580 --> 00:17:38,880
I don’t really know if love is a waste of time or not, but...

204
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:43,240
I know what I had was definitely a huge waste of time.

205
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:45,600
Goodbye.

206
00:17:47,570 --> 00:17:49,840
That’ll be 1,000 won (about 80 cents).

207
00:17:59,420 --> 00:18:00,190
What is this?

208
00:18:00,190 --> 00:18:01,720
My phone number.

209
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:07,610
Do not misunderstand me, I'm not into you. I'm looking for a part-time job.

210
00:18:16,850 --> 00:18:18,560
Thank you.

211
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:21,110
Goodbye.

212
00:18:24,460 --> 00:18:26,810
One Cobb salad and spaghetti aglio e olio.

213
00:18:26,810 --> 00:18:28,490
Yes, sir.

214
00:18:28,490 --> 00:18:30,360
Hello?

215
00:18:31,950 --> 00:18:33,800
Hello?

216
00:18:34,910 --> 00:18:40,850
I’m the person who caused a ruckus yesterday in front of the barbecue restaurant.

217
00:18:44,530 --> 00:18:46,360
Well...

218
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:51,470
Anyway, I’m sorry about yesterday.

219
00:18:51,470 --> 00:18:55,530
So just think of it as a really bad experience,  and please erase it from your memory.

220
00:18:55,530 --> 00:18:57,330
Bye.

221
00:19:13,090 --> 00:19:13,920
Hello?

222
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:16,160
You called to tell me that?

223
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:18,800
Well, kind of.

224
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:22,250
I wanted to ask you for a favor, but I thought I probably shouldn’t.

225
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:25,500
- I’m sorry.
- Ah, hold on. Wait a sec.

226
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:29,870
If you called perhaps because you need a part-timer, feel free to tell me.

227
00:19:29,870 --> 00:19:32,390
I’ll do anything for money.

228
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:40,210
You told me that you even give evening calls, right?

229
00:19:40,210 --> 00:19:43,800
Yes, that’s right. I do anything for money.

230
00:19:46,890 --> 00:19:52,650
Then could you sing for me?

231
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:55,600
- Sing?
- Yes.

232
00:19:55,630 --> 00:20:00,550
It’s actually better if you're bad at singing. It will help me fall asleep.

233
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:06,510
So you’re saying...

234
00:20:06,510 --> 00:20:11,100
even if I can't sing, you want me to sing personally for you?

235
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:12,590
I know it sounds weird.

236
00:20:12,590 --> 00:20:15,970
But even sleeping pills don’t work.

237
00:20:15,970 --> 00:20:17,950
It doesn’t necessarily have to be you either.

238
00:20:17,950 --> 00:20:20,550
Let me know if there’s anyone who’s willing to do it for me.

239
00:20:20,550 --> 00:20:22,520
I’m a pro at that. What time should I call you?

240
00:20:22,520 --> 00:20:24,080
What?

241
00:20:25,050 --> 00:20:27,000
Oh, tonight?

242
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:32,710
Well... about midnight?

243
00:20:32,710 --> 00:20:35,470
Then I’ll call you tonight at 11:50 p.m.

244
00:20:35,470 --> 00:20:39,480
If you successfully fall asleep after hearing me sing, you can officially hire me starting tomorrow.

245
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:43,460
If you fail to fall asleep, you can just forget everything. How does that sound?

246
00:20:45,180 --> 00:20:48,760
Well, it sounds like a good deal.

247
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:51,710
Okay, then I’ll call you at 11:50 p.m.

248
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:06,790
What did I just do?

249
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:16,420
I hope you enjoy your time.

250
00:21:45,730 --> 00:21:51,950
There is a private secret hidden in Shostakovich's Symphony No. 10, my favorite piece.

251
00:21:51,950 --> 00:21:54,540
What is the secret?

252
00:21:56,700 --> 00:22:04,300
D, E Flat, C, and B are played by the timpani

253
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:08,150
If you change the spelling to German spelling,
(in German D, Es, C, H, pronounced as "De-Es-Ce-Ha"),

254
00:22:08,150 --> 00:22:12,930
they become the composer's initials.
(in German "Dmitri Schostakowitsch": D. Sch., also pronounced as "De-Es-Ce-Ha.)

255
00:22:12,930 --> 00:22:17,200
I also have a secret.

256
00:22:18,350 --> 00:22:21,690
My secret is the summer of last year.

257
00:22:21,690 --> 00:22:26,760
So... I don't remember the summer when I was 26.

258
00:22:29,130 --> 00:22:33,020
While riding a taxi, I was in a traffic accident

259
00:22:33,020 --> 00:22:37,510
and my memory of the three months which followed disappeared.

260
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:44,560
It is three months.

261
00:22:44,560 --> 00:22:48,220
Well, sometimes I do have flights of fancy.

262
00:22:48,220 --> 00:22:51,400
In the memory which disappeared,

263
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:55,660
there may or may not be a huge hidden secret, which I don't know.

264
00:23:01,120 --> 00:23:03,980
No, that's going overboard.

265
00:23:03,980 --> 00:23:10,560
In any case, whatever is in that memory, could it be more terrible than my present reality?

266
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:32,450
Hello.

267
00:23:32,450 --> 00:23:35,310
Have you thought it over?
What song do you want to hear?

268
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:39,590
Give me a sec. Let me catch my breath.

269
00:23:42,460 --> 00:23:45,900
So, you're going to sing me a song?

270
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:50,430
If you don't have a special request, I'm going to sing whatever I want.

271
00:23:51,890 --> 00:23:53,800
I see.

272
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:59,400
In that case, it's "One Man." Kim Jong Gook's "One Man."

273
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:05,000
"One Man", that's good. Alright then.

274
00:24:05,060 --> 00:24:07,820
Then I will begin the song.

275
00:24:10,460 --> 00:24:17,020
♫ It must have been a long time

276
00:24:17,020 --> 00:24:25,260
♫  almost enough  to make what I'm saying colorless

277
00:24:25,260 --> 00:24:28,930
♫ Just looking into your eyes

278
00:24:28,930 --> 00:24:36,160
♫ like your friend who knows everything about you

279
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:40,010
♫ like your shadow

280
00:24:40,010 --> 00:24:42,420
♫ it seems we were always together

281
00:24:42,500 --> 00:24:45,740
What in the world—
I can't believe that.

282
00:24:45,740 --> 00:24:48,490
He can't sing even that song.

283
00:24:48,490 --> 00:24:54,340
♫ When you're struggling or sad

284
00:24:54,340 --> 00:24:58,370
♫ or when you're lonely too

285
00:24:58,370 --> 00:25:01,560
♫ Because you're suffering from us being apart.

286
00:25:01,560 --> 00:25:04,000
♫ If you're hurting too,

287
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:08,750
♫ I'll wipe away your tears

288
00:25:08,750 --> 00:25:12,370
♫ There's one man.

289
00:25:12,370 --> 00:25:16,070
♫ He loved you so much.

290
00:25:16,070 --> 00:25:19,580
♫ There is one man.

291
00:25:19,580 --> 00:25:24,590
♫  Unable to say "I love you"

292
00:25:24,590 --> 00:25:27,370
♫ He'll be at your side and he'll extend his hand

293
00:25:27,370 --> 00:25:31,000
- But it's weird.
-♫ so surely it will be within your reach

294
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:34,530
- While listening to his strange singing
♫ Cherishing you more than myself,

295
00:25:34,530 --> 00:25:37,770
my agitated mind is calmed.

296
00:25:37,770 --> 00:25:42,440
For the past few days I've been having a hard time.
♫ I am here, holding you.

297
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:45,600
♫ I think am going crazy

298
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:53,500
♫ and suddenly I want to hug you.

299
00:25:53,500 --> 00:25:57,270
♫ There is a woman.

300
00:25:57,270 --> 00:26:01,200
♫ While receiving  love she may not know know it's love

301
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:05,350
♫ I am crying but

302
00:26:06,330 --> 00:26:10,400
♫ I am happy

303
00:26:20,730 --> 00:26:22,580
Hello?

304
00:26:23,830 --> 00:26:25,600
Hello.

305
00:26:36,110 --> 00:26:38,060
What is this?

306
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:41,990
Jeez.

307
00:27:05,620 --> 00:27:12,310
One Year Ago

308
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:47,720
Report for the rescue application, there is a death.

309
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:50,600
He is a man in his twenties,

310
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:53,570
